Notification of Operating Procedure Update

*	The following new or revised ISO Operating Procedures have been
implemented and are posted for reference on the ISO Website.

ISO Operating Procedure posted:  T-122A WEST OF BORAH VERSUS PATH 15
NOMOGRAM with attachment A
Version: 1.7
Effective Date: 6-28-01
Procedure Purpose: California Independent System Operator (CAISO) system
dispatchers will implement the following procedure in real-time.  The
Nomograms will cover all four operating seasons.
Changes / Reasons:  Nomogram updates for IRAS and 300 MW criteria remained
effective.

*	Please find them at
http://www1.caiso.com/thegrid/operations/opsdoc/index.html under the
appropriate Operating Procedure section heading.

